<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,657,683]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Remarks.</emphasis>
It is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[497,679,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stirellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picinus">
<emphasis box="[497,679,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Stirellus picinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it can be distinguished by the truncate hind margin of female sternite VII, by the upturned apex of the male pygofer lobe and the tapered aedeagal apex (in posterior view) with elongate gonopore.
</paragraph>
